        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 7:44PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 744 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Semora, or 11 miles southwest of Turbeville, moving southeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roxboro, Concord, Bushy Fork, Hyco Lake, Moriah, Hyco Marina, Surl,
and Mayo Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
